  "transcript": [
    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 1.86,
      "end": 7.88,
      "text": "This is a LibraVox Recording. All LibraVox recordings are in the public domain. For more",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 7.88,
      "end": 15.02,
      "text": "information or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org. This reading by Henry Frigon.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 16.8,
      "end": 25.54,
      "text": "Spaceman3000.blogspot.com. Asip's Fables. The Hair and the Taurus by Asip. A hair was",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 25.54,
      "end": 29.32,
      "text": "one day making fun of a tortoise for being so slow upon his feet.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 30.18,
      "end": 35.88,
      "text": "Wait a bit, said the tortoise. I'll run a race with you, and I'll wager that I win.\"",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 35.88,
      "end": 42.18,
      "text": "O well replied the hair, who was much amused at the idea. Let's try and see. And it was",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 42.18,
      "end": 48.92,
      "text": "soon agreed that the fox should set a course for them and be the judge. When it came time",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 48.92,
      "end": 53.82,
      "text": "both started off together, but the hair was soon so far ahead that he thought he might",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 53.82,
      "end": 57.84,
      "text": "as well have a rest, so down he lay and fell fast asleep.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 59.06,
      "end": 65.94,
      "text": "Meanwhile the tortoise kept plotting along and in time reached the goal. At last the hair",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 65.94,
      "end": 73.6,
      "text": "woke up with a start and dashed at his fastest, only to find that the tortoise had already won",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 73.6,
      "end": 81.12,
      "text": "the race. Slow and steady wins the race. And of the hair and the tortoise,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 81.12,
      "end": 87.5,
      "text": "read on February 13th, 2006 in Oceanside, California.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
